chunk_content: Note: Retesting for verification of HIV-positive status before or at antiretroviral (ART) treatment initiation is only done for persons who have already been diagnosed HIV- positive as per the national HIV testing guidelines. All clients diagnosed HIV-positive should be retested for verification before or at ART initiation with a new specimen and preferably a second operator using the same national HIV testing strategy. Retesting for verification is primarily done as a quality assurance activity to avoid misdiagnosis and to ensure those initiated on ART and treatment services are indeed HIV-positive. Thus, HIV testing conducted to verify one’s HIV- positive status should not be counted under HTS_TST, since the initial HIV diagnosis will have already been counted at the point of the initial receipt of the HIV diagnosis. 4.
